docs.abstract: HopStop, the transit app owned by Apple, is no longer available for download. But Citymapper remains one of the best apps for finding your way in New York City.
docs.snippet: HopStop, the transit app owned by Apple, is no longer available for download. But Citymapper remains one of the best apps for finding your way in New York City.
docs.lead_paragraph: HopStop, until recently the go-to app for New York’s savviest subway navigators, is nearing the end of the line. It has been owned by Apple for two years, and as of this month, it is no longer featured in the App Store. For those who have the app, it continues to operate at the time of this writing, but now the core of HopStop’s transit directions has been folded into the Maps application of the newest iPhone operating system.

headline.main: As HopStop Nears End of the Line, Transfer to Citymapper

docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — Apple has disabled its news app in China, according to a person with direct knowledge of the situation, the most recent sign of how difficult it can be for foreign companies to manage the strict rules governing media and online expression there.
